storm2013.utilities
Class BangBangController

java.lang.Object
  storm2013.utilities.BangBangController
All Implemented Interfaces:
LiveWindowSendable, IDevice, IUtility, Sendable
public class BangBangController
extends Object
implements IUtility, LiveWindowSendable

The BangBangController has three parts: When the speed of the motor (found through the IEncoderSpeed interface which just gives the controller the motor speed in RPM) is less than _spinUpPoint, the PIDOutput will be set to _spinUpSpeed. When the speed gets up to _spinUpPoint but is still less than _setPoint, the output will be set to _maxSpeed. Once the speed reaches the _setPoint, the output is set to zero, allowing the motor to simply coast. This is done to conserve energy and to reduce strain on the motors.

The default (and only, at the moment) constructor.

Parameters:
PIDOut - The PIDOutput that the controller outputs to.
SpeedCalculator - The class that implements IEncoderSpeed so that this controller can get the speed of the motor.
table - The ITable that the controller should report its values to and retrieve values from.
setPoint - The speed (RPM) that you want the motor to go.
spinUpPoint - The point at which the motor switches from the spin up speed to the max speed.
spinUpSpeed - The speed the motor should spin at (RPM) while on its way to the spin up point.
maxSpeed - The speed the motor should spin at (RPM) once it's passed the spin up point but hasn't yet reached the set point.
period - The period between executions of go(). (If you don't know what to make it, go for about 50, which makes it run 20 times a second).
See Also:
PIDOutput, IEncoderSpeed, ITable
